Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["ForgetAllMemo", "ObjectName",ExpressionUUID->"2ac8f2a3-20cd-44a5-893a-2a0503949be6"],

Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell[TextData[{
     StyleBox["ForgetAllMemo", "TI"],
     " \[LineSeparator]While HyperIntica is the main (analytic) integration \
routine working under the hood of the STIntegrate function, it can also be \
used as a standalone function."
    }], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"6314cc6a-8ec9-4cf7-9998-52b03f83ed80"]}
  },
  GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Left}}},
  GridBoxItemSize->{
   "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}]], "Usage",
 CellID->1,ExpressionUUID->"1cddd15c-2510-461d-909b-945cd88bc7d7"],

Cell["\<\
While HyperIntica is the main (analytic) integration routine working under \
the hood of the STIntegrate function, it can also be used as a standalone \
function. It evaluates iterated integrals \[Integral]_0^\[Infinity] \
\[Ellipsis] \[Integral]_0^\[Infinity] f\\, dx_1 \[Ellipsis] dx_n in  for \
expressions built from hyperlogarithms, polylogarithms, logarithms, and \
rational functions, returning results in terms of multi-zeta values and \
hyperlogarithms in the original integrand f parameters (if any). The syntax \
is: (see example below)\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"36e96b1e-99d6-4e96-97fa-e8307961ed13"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
  RowBox[{"integrand", ",", " ", "variables", ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Monitor\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "False"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",Exp\
ressionUUID->"09a974a2-9615-4fad-a517-cab776fc0501"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Details", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8a5a0352-9a3f-4f23-9e40-b0387222e1a0"],

Cell["Memoization and cache management", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"228dccaa-0b94-496b-b657-42f426326f8e"],

Cell["\<\
During integration, {HyperIntica} accumulates several internal memoization \
caches. These persist for the duration of the session, which is beneficial \
when evaluating many related integrals, and can be cleared at any time by \
calling ForgetAllMemo in the notebook where calculations are done.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ddb77dcd-bc3f-4143-92d1-5528cfddb92d"]
}, Open  ]],

